This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses curriculum learning, which is a technique used in machine learning to improve the training process, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which are a common tool in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions minibatch bucketing, which is a technique used in optimization algorithms, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses English-to-Czech translation as an example, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
